</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9A3036FDFFFB215AFCABCE6B6D8BBFF9" blockId="47.[826,1441,1636,1903]" lastBlockId="48.[144,759,198,740]" lastPageId="48" lastPageNumber="299" pageId="47" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis id="A8FBEAEFFFFB2145FCABCE6B6C94BB67" box="[826,954,1637,1658]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="298">Discussion:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="FE1E4B0CFFFB2145FC58CE6A6B4DBB67" author="Arndt" box="[969,1123,1636,1658]" pageId="47" pageNumber="298" pagination="110 - 119" refId="ref38573" refString="Arndt W. 1913. Zoologische Ergebnisse der ersten Lehr- Expedition der P. Scottlanderschen Jubilaums-Stifting. Jahresberichte der Schlesischen Gesellschaft fur vaterlandische Cultur 90: 110 - 119." type="journal article" year="1913">Arndt (1913)</bibRefCitation>
identified with hesitation a small specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="E298766DFFFB2145FBF1CE8D6B97BB85" box="[1120,1209,1667,1688]" name="Norway" pageId="47" pageNumber="298">Norway</collectingCountry>
as 
<taxonomicName id="5D8F4D7EFFFB2145FB7ECE8D6A49BB85" authorityName=", Schmidt" authorityYear="1870" box="[1263,1383,1667,1688]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Geodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="47" pageNumber="298" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="A8FBEAEFFFFB2145FB7ECE8D6A49BB85" box="[1263,1383,1667,1688]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="298">G. simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the specimen has not been located. 
<bibRefCitation id="FE1E4B0CFFFB2145FB24CEAC6A75BBAA" author="Burton M" box="[1205,1371,1697,1719]" pageId="47" pageNumber="298" pagination="856 - 860" refId="ref39454" refString="Burton M. 1946. Notes on certain species of Geodia described by Oscar Schmidt. Annals and Magazine of Natural History Ser. 11, xiii: 856 - 860." type="journal article" year="1946">Burton (1946)</bibRefCitation>
, after an examination of spicule preparations from the type material from 
<collectingCountry id="E298766DFFFB2145FC79CED06B4DBBE9" box="[1000,1123,1758,1780]" name="Greenland" pageId="47" pageNumber="298">Greenland</collectingCountry>
, concluded that 
<taxonomicName id="5D8F4D7EFFFB2145FABBCED16A8FBBEE" authorityName=", Schmidt" authorityYear="1870" box="[1322,1441,1758,1780]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Geodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="47" pageNumber="298" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="A8FBEAEFFFFB2145FABBCED16A8FBBEE" box="[1322,1441,1758,1780]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="298">G. simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is probably identical to 
<taxonomicName id="5D8F4D7EFFFB2145FBC2CEF36BCDBA0F" authorityName=", Gorbunov" authorityYear="1946" box="[1107,1251,1789,1810]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Geodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="47" pageNumber="298" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="cydonium">
<emphasis id="A8FBEAEFFFFB2145FBC2CEF36BCDBA0F" box="[1107,1251,1789,1810]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="298">G. cydonium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which explains why 
<bibRefCitation id="FE1E4B0CFFFB2145FCE7CF126B34BA2C" author="Burton M" box="[886,1050,1819,1841]" pageId="47" pageNumber="298" pagination="1 - 71" refId="ref39558" refString="Burton M. 1959. Spongia. In: Fridriksson A, Tuxen SL, eds. The zoology of Iceland. Copenhagen: Ejnar Munksgaard, 1 - 71." type="book chapter" year="1959">Burton (1959)</bibRefCitation>
later mentioned 
<taxonomicName id="5D8F4D7EFFFB2145FB7DCF126A52BA2C" authorityName=", Gorbunov" authorityYear="1946" box="[1260,1404,1820,1841]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Geodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="47" pageNumber="298" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="cydonium">
<emphasis id="A8FBEAEFFFFB2145FB7DCF126A52BA2C" box="[1260,1404,1820,1841]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="298">G. cydonium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as occurring in 
<collectingCountry id="E298766DFFFB2145FC4DCF346B7ABA4D" box="[988,1108,1850,1872]" name="Greenland" pageId="47" pageNumber="298">Greenland</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="E298766DFFFB2145FB0FCF356BD6BA4D" box="[1182,1272,1851,1872]" name="Norway" pageId="47" pageNumber="298">Norway</collectingCountry>
. Also, 
<bibRefCitation id="FE1E4B0CFFFB2145FAC3CF346C80BA72" author="Koltun VM" pageId="47" pageNumber="298" pagination="1 - 112" refId="ref41717" refString="Koltun VM. 1966. Four-rayed sponges of Northern and Far Eastern seas of the USSR (order Tetraxonida). Opredeliti Faunei SSSR 90. (Zoological Institute of the Academy of Sciences of the USSR: Moscow, Leningrad): 1 - 112, pls I - XXXVIII (in Russian)." type="book chapter" year="1966">Koltun (1966: 57)</bibRefCitation>
doubted the existence of 
<taxonomicName id="5D8F4D7EFFFB2145FB4ECF576A79BA73" authorityName=", Schmidt" authorityYear="1870" box="[1247,1367,1881,1902]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Geodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="47" pageNumber="298" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="A8FBEAEFFFFB2145FB4ECF576A79BA73" box="[1247,1367,1881,1902]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="298">G. simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as an independent species. We have inspected the 
<typeStatus id="4534885FFFE4215AFD1EC8C86DDCBDC1" box="[655,754,198,220]" pageId="48" pageNumber="299">holotype</typeStatus>
, a whole specimen cut in two. It is a rounded lump, measuring 
<emphasis id="A8FBEAEFFFE4215AFE84C90A6E0EBC04" box="[277,288,260,281]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="299">c</emphasis>
. 
<quantity id="5D779B18FFE4215AFEA2C90A6E47BC04" box="[307,361,260,281]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="48" pageNumber="299" unit="cm" value="7.0">7 cm</quantity>
in diameter and 
<quantity id="5D779B18FFE4215AFDD3C90D6D59BC04" box="[578,631,259,281]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="48" pageNumber="299" unit="cm" value="3.0">3 cm</quantity>
in height; the surface is damaged in some areas, and algae are growing on it. The cortex is 
<quantity id="5D779B18FFE4215AFE4CC94E6D30BC4B" box="[477,542,320,342]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="48" pageNumber="299" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
thick. The spicule repertoire is clearly that of 
<taxonomicName id="5D8F4D7EFFE4215AFE7EC9516D51BC69" authorityName=", Gorbunov" authorityYear="1946" box="[495,639,351,372]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Geodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="48" pageNumber="299" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="cydonium">
<emphasis id="A8FBEAEFFFE4215AFE7EC9516D51BC69" box="[495,639,351,372]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="299">G. cydonium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Mediterranean Sea. However, there must be a mistake, most likely from Schmidt’s side, as the label is in his handwriting. The algae growing on the specimen do not occur in 
<collectingCountry id="E298766DFFE4215AFE29C9D76D1DBCF2" box="[440,563,473,495]" name="Greenland" pageId="48" pageNumber="299">Greenland</collectingCountry>
; on the contrary, one of the species is Mediterranean, another one Mediterranean–southern boreal (Dr Poul Møller Pedersen, pers. comm.). We therefore confirm that 
<taxonomicName id="5D8F4D7EFFE4215AFF01CA5A6E29BF74" authorityName=", Schmidt" authorityYear="1870" box="[144,263,596,617]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Geodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="48" pageNumber="299" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="A8FBEAEFFFE4215AFF01CA5A6E29BF74" box="[144,263,596,617]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="299">G. simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="5D8F4D7EFFE4215AFDA6CA5A6DE9BF74" authorityName=", Gorbunov" authorityYear="1946" box="[567,711,596,617]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Geodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="48" pageNumber="299" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="cydonium">
<emphasis id="A8FBEAEFFFE4215AFDA6CA5A6DE9BF74" box="[567,711,596,617]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="299">G. cydonium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As molecular results suggest that 
<taxonomicName id="5D8F4D7EFFE4215AFDB1CA7C6D9EBF9A" authorityName=", Gorbunov" authorityYear="1946" box="[544,688,626,647]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Geodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="48" pageNumber="299" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="cydonium">
<emphasis id="A8FBEAEFFFE4215AFDB1CA7C6D9EBF9A" box="[544,688,626,647]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="299">G. cydonium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a species complex (
<bibRefCitation id="FE1E4B0CFFE4215AFECBCA9F6D7ABFBA" author="Cardenas P &amp; Xavier JR &amp; Reveillaud J &amp; Schander C &amp; Rapp HT" box="[346,596,657,679]" pageId="48" pageNumber="299" pagination="18318" refId="ref39750" refString="Cardenas P, Xavier JR, Reveillaud J, Schander C, Rapp HT. 2011. Molecular phylogeny of the Astrophorida (Porifera, Demospongiae) reveals an unexpected high level of spicule homoplasy. PLoS ONE 6: e 18318." type="journal article" year="2011">
Cárdenas 
<emphasis id="A8FBEAEFFFE4215AFE43CA9F6D2DBFBB" box="[466,515,657,678]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="299">et al</emphasis>
., 2011
</bibRefCitation>
), only a thorough morphological revision of this complex will tell us to which species group 
<taxonomicName id="5D8F4D7EFFE4215AFE56CAC06D11BFFE" authorityName=", Schmidt" authorityYear="1870" box="[455,575,718,739]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Geodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="48" pageNumber="299" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="A8FBEAEFFFE4215AFE56CAC06D11BFFE" box="[455,575,718,739]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="299">G. simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs.
</paragraph>
